  "response": "The word \"intimation\" refers to a hint or indirect suggestion. Here are examples of how it can be used in a sentence:\n\n- \"He received an intimation that the company might be downsizing soon.\"\n- \"Her smile was an intimation that she was pleased with the outcome.\"\n- \"The intimation of trouble was enough to make everyone cautious.\"\n- \"Through intimation, he indicated that he was not pleased with their decision.\"\n\nThese examples show how \"intimation\" can imply subtle or indirect communication.",
